Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pick the leaves from their stalks and finely chop
(discard the stalks). Pop the @butternut squash{200%g}(diced) onto a lined
#baking tray{} and drizzle on a splash of oil. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} and sprinkle on half the @sage{1/2}(leaves picked and finely chopped).
Use your hands to rub the flavours all over the squash. Roast on the top shelf
of your oven until soft and golden, ~{17-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through
cooking.

Fill a large #saucepan{} with @water{750%ml} and pop onto medium heat to slowly
come to the boil. Stir in and dissolve the @vegetable stock powder{1}. Meanwhile,
halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and
grate the @garlic{1%clove}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the
@hazelnuts{25%g}(roughly chopped).

Heat a splash of @oil{} in another large saucepan on medium-high heat. Add the
onion and a pinch of salt and pepper. Stir and cook until the onion is soft and
caramelised, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir in the @dried Italian herbs{1/2%tsp} and
garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Pour in the @Arborio rice{175%g} and stir
together. Cook and stir for ~{1%minute} so the rice is coated in the garlicky
oil. Add the @white wine vinegar{12%ml} and allow it to evaporate.

Add a ladleful of the stock and stir. Once the rice has absorbed the stock, add
another ladleful and repeat. Continue adding ladlefuls of stock, stirring
regularly until it has all been absorbed by the rice. This should take
~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: Let the rice absorb each ladleful of stock before adding the next.

When the squash is ready, remove from your oven and transfer to a #bowl{}. Use a
#fork{} to mash it to a rough purée. Add to the risotto as soon as it is ready
and keep cooking and stirring until all of the stock has been used.

> TIP: The risotto is done when the rice is 'al dente' - cooked through but with
> a bit of firmness left.

Stir the @baby spinach{125%g} in a handful at a time until wilted then add the
remaining sage.

Halve the @lemon{1} and add a squeeze of juice to the risotto. Season to taste
with salt and pepper. Pop the @wild rocket{40%g} in a large bowl and drizzle on
a splash of @olive oil{} and a squeeze of remaining lemon juice. Toss and get
ready to serve. Spoon the risotto into deep bowls and top with the rocket.
Finish with a sprinkling of hazelnuts. Enjoy!